PART ONE, MOVING FROM BUILDIN AN ENTIRE WALLET, TO MIDDLEMAN LOGIC


Perfect choice. Moving as a Middle Man is significantly more scalable and carries much less regulatory risk. We will position the app as a "Subscription Firewall" for businesses.

Here is exactly what I am going to do to upgrade the system to this model:

1. Update the Data Model (
type.ts
)
I will replace the "Internal Wallet" concept with a FundingSource.
This represents the real bank account or credit card that is "behind" the mask.
2. Upgrade the Transaction Engine (
CardMasker.ts
)
The "Fund Check": Before approving a payment, the system will now perform two checks:
Rule Check: (Does it pass the Merchant Lock and Virtual Card limit?)
Upstream Check: (Does the linked "Real Card" have enough money?)
Automatic Top-up Logic: We will simulate the "Pull" from the real bank account.
3. Business-Specific Controls
I will add "Subscription Guard" logic. For example, if a business only wants to spend $50/month on AWS, the card will automatically "Reset" its limit every month but never allow an overage.
